## 0. Simple web stack infrastructure description

This infrastructure consists of a single server hosting a website accessible via www.foobar.com.

### Components logic:
- The user accesses the website by typing the domain name in the browser.
- DNS translates the domain name www.foobar.com (A record) to the server IP 8.8.8.8.
- The Web Server (Nginx) receives the HTTP request and communicates with the Application Server.
- The Application Server executes the code logic from the Application Files.
- The Database (MySQL) stores and provides the necessary data.
- Communication between the client and server happens via HTTP over TCP/IP.

### Issues:
- SPOF: If the server fails, the entire stack is down.
- Maintenance: Deployments or restarts cause downtime.
- Scaling: Single server resources are limited and cannot handle high traffic spikes.
